modules.description: Provides methods for displaying native dialog boxes, including alerts, confirmations, and prompts, with callback handling for user responses. Works with strings, booleans, and integers to customize dialog content and behavior. Used to request user confirmation before performing critical actions or to display error messages with actionable feedback.

Provides functions to display alerts, confirmations, and prompts with customizable titles, button labels, and callback handlers, and to trigger a beep sound. Works with strings, arrays of strings, and a custom button_response type to represent user input. Used to handle user interactions in mobile applications, such as confirming actions or collecting text input.
